screen_name: EPDXO
full_text
Ok but my attitude? I needa chill

You’re wrong. This is serious. It  couldve gone so much worse for me especially since I have asthma (& it was already sucky) I am a nurse so I knew I was putting myself at risk and it was only a matter of time.

It was definitely a roller coaster of symptoms which different intensities each day which was scary because I didn’t know what to expect. Having trouble breathing is no fun . So for those who think its not big deal and that because you are young youll be fine ..
Day 14: Felt like myself!!! Energy was back and runny nose was less runny! No more cough . Feeling in the clear!
Day 13: I felt good! All that I had was a runny nose & some slight back pain
Day 12: This day felt more like I had allergies. I had a runny nose & wad sneezing but overall energetic!! (Yay!)
Day 11 : heachace , cough, stuffy/ runny nose , dizzy, nauseous & SOB (I was confused since I was feeling better day before. This day sucked, I thought I was going to get sicker)

Day 3: HEADACHE , fatigued but able to shift in bed, light cough not as constant still as deep , stuffy nose and no more sore throat

Day 9 : Slight cough, stuffy nose, still no smell or taste (didn’t have any smell or taste since day 3 ) breathing was okay unless I talked too much , cough would get worse .
Day 8 : Felt almost back to normal, had a rush of energy , still have the cough , and body aches over all but definitely felt the difference (got so excited! Knew I was half way through! )
Day 7 : Chest hurts especially when trying to breathe, FATIGUE , cough is back to being constant
Day 5: I woke up with more energy than day before. Headache is tolerable, cough is still deep but less constant , no fever. When breathing chest and ribs hurt like a stabbing feel.
